My general feeling is that this is quite dense, especially with all the static calls to the object base class. I through together a simple first approach. What are the deficiencies of the following?
```python
class COWProxy(object):
    __slots__ = ('_obj', '_partial', '_partial_dict', '_copied')

    def __init__(self, obj, partial=False):
        self._obj = obj
        self._partial = partial
        self._partial_dict = {}
        self._copied = False

    def __getattribute__(self, attr):
        if self._copied:
            return getattr(self._obj, attr)
        return self._partial_dict.setdefault(attr, COWProxy(getattr(self._obj, attr)))

    def __setattr__(self, attr, value):
        if self._copied:
            return setattr(self._obj, attr, value)
        if not self._partial:
            self._obj = deepcopy(self._obj)
            self._copied = True
            return setattr(self._obj, attr, value)
        self._partial_dict[attr] = value
```

